name: Arasbaran
description:
In antiquity, this region was inhabited by the Alarodians and Caspian tribes.
Armenia, Mesopotamia, Babylonia and Assyria with Adjacent Regions", Karl von Spruner, published in 1865.
Then this area became alternately part of the Medes and Persia. In the 2nd century B.C. the region became part of the Armenian kingdom, where the Armenian principality Parspatunik was established, which existed until the 6th century A.D.
Small Armenian melikdoms of Karadagh (Arasbaran) remained until the Turkish invasion of 1918. The Armenian population is preserved in the mountains of Arasbaran(Karadagh) in modern day
